
[1]button-stone

   BUT'TON-STONE, n. A species of figured stone, or hard flint, resembling
   a button, consisting of two bodies which appear to be the filling up of
   holes in a shell. A species has been found finely striated, like a
   mohair button. This name is given also to a species of slate found in
   the marquisate of Bareith.
